  "notes": "Novial — constructed international auxiliary language published by the Danish linguist Otto Jespersen (1928). Near-phonemic Latin orthography; ⟨w⟩ is not used in the standard spelling. ⟨j⟩ = /dʒ/ (or /ʒ/), ⟨y⟩ = the glide /j/, ⟨ch⟩ = /tʃ/, ⟨sh⟩ = /ʃ/, ⟨z⟩ = /ts/ (some speakers /z/), ⟨x⟩ = the cluster /ks/. ⟨c⟩ is /k/ except before front vowels, where it is /s/. Five cardinal vowels a e i o u.",
